description.en-US:
The classic Battleship Game should have:
- 4 ships with one cell;
- 3 ships with 2 cells;
- 2 ships with 3 cells;
- 1 ship with 4 cells. 

All ships must be straight, not bent and "diagonal". Ships are located on the playing field in such a way that there is always a gap between them. They should not touch each other neither sides nor corners. In this case, the ships can touch the edges of the field and occupy the corners.

The Battleship Game begins after all the ships have taken their positions. Click on the empty cells on the opponent's field and try to destroy all of his ships.

The Battleship Game is played until the complete victory of one of the players, that is, until all the ships of the opponent are sunk.
